{"questionId":"1250131","questionHtml":"<p>An electric motor raises an object of weight <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math> through a vertical distance of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>. The current in the electric motor is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> at a potential difference of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>. What is the efficiency of the electric motor?</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>17</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>38</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>75</mn><mo> </mo><mo>%</mo></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"1250131","referenceCode":"20N.1A.SL.TZ0.19","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"An electric motor raises an object of weight 500 N through a vertical distance of 3.0 m in 1.5 s. The current in the electric motor is 10 A at a potential difference of 200 V. What","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"19","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["B. The particulate nature of matter","B.5 Current and circuits","A. Space, time and motion","A.3 Work, energy and power"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}